This paper discusses the use of distributed controllers in SDN deployments, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses consistency models and clustering techniques, which are commonly used in distributed systems (cs.DC) and databases (cs.DB). The adaptation strategy presented in the paper involves mapping application performance indicators to consistency levels, which could be considered a form of machine learning or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the overall system performance and optimization, which could be classified under systems and control (cs.SY).
